recipieName: Fried egg on toast with apple, yogurt & latte
recipeIngredients:
• Extra virgin olive oil, 1 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Eggs, 1 large (1.8oz)
  • Whole-grain bread, 1 slice(s), toasted (1.1oz)
  • Sriracha, 1 tsp(s), optional (0.2oz)
  • Apple, 1 small (5.3oz)
  • Non-fat plain Greek yogurt, ⅓ cup(s) (2.6oz)
  • Latte, plain, nonfat milk, 1 small takeaway cup(s) (11.5oz)
recipeInstructions:
Heat the oil in a non-stick pan over medium heat. Once the oil is hot, crack the egg into the pan. Cook for 3 minutes, or until cooked to your liking.

Remove the egg from the pan and place on top of warm toasted bread. Drizzle over sriracha, if using.

Enjoy with a sliced apple dipped in yogurt.

Follow with a skim latte.

  • Moroccan seasoning, 1 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Rye crispbread, 4 crispbread(s) (1.4oz)

recipeInstructions:

recipeIngredients:
• Beef tenderloin steak, any grade, very lean, 3 oz(s) (3oz)
  • Extra virgin olive oil, 1 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Garlic, minced, 1 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Ginger, minced, 1 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Green beans, trimmed, 1 cup(s), chopped (3.5oz)
  • Green onion, 1 medium, sliced (0.5oz)
  • Sesame seeds, 1 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Arugula, 1½ cup(s) (1.1oz)
recipeInstructions:
Season steak to taste.

Heat a non-stick frying pan on medium-high heat and cook steak for 3 to 4 minutes each side, or until cooked to your liking. Remove from pan and cover.

Clean frying pan and heat to medium-high. Add olive oil, garlic, ginger and green beans. Stir fry for 1 to 2 minutes. Turn off heat and add onions and sesame seeds. Continue to toss for another 30 seconds.

On a serving plate, place green beans on a bed of arugula and serve steak along side.

TIP: Slice the steak into strips and toss with arugula and beans to enjoy as a salad.

recipeIngredients:
• Extra virgin olive oil, 4 tsp(s) (0.6oz)
  • Baby carrot, 8 medium, scrubbed and cut lengthways (2.8oz)
  • Red bell pepper, raw, 1 medium, cut into thick slices (4.2oz)
  • Instant brown rice, cooked, 1⅓ cup(s) (9.9oz)
  • Baby spinach, 2 cup(s) (1.3oz)
  • Green onion, 2 medium, finely sliced (1.1oz)
  • Hummus, ½ cup(s) (4.2oz)
  • Parsley, fresh, 2 handful(s), roughly chopped (2.1oz)
  • Lemon, ½ medium, zest and juice (1.5oz)
  • Paprika, ½ tsp(s)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Hummus bliss bowl according to recipe instructions below.

Enjoy one serving for lunch and store the remaining rice and vegetables in an airtight container in the fridge for lunch later in the week.

Hummus bliss bowl instructions

Preheat the oven to 350°F. Rub the oil over the carrots and peppers. Add only the carrots to a roasting pan and roast in the oven for 20 minutes. Carefully add the red pepper slices to the pan, and cook for a further 10 minutes. Remove from the oven and set aside to cool.

Prepare the rice according to packet instructions.

Into a bowl, add the rice, spinach, roasted vegetables, and green onion. Top with the hummus, parsley, and lemon zest. Squeeze over the lemon juice and sprinkle with a pinch of paprika prior to serving.

recipieName: Mezze plate with falafels, grilled vegetables & homemade hummus
recipeIngredients:
• Red bell pepper, raw, 2 medium, sliced (8.4oz)
  • Asparagus, 1 bunch(es), trimmed (4oz)
  • Zucchini, 2 medium, cut into sticks (13.8oz)
  • Canned chickpeas, 1½ cup(s), drained and rinsed (8.7oz)
  • Extra virgin olive oil, 2 tbsp(s) (1oz)
  • Lemon, ½ medium, juiced and zested for hummus (1.5oz)
  • Cilantro, fresh, ¼ cup(s) (0.2oz)
  • Psyllium husk, 1 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Garlic, minced, 2 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Cumin, ground, ½ tsp(s)
  • Allspice, ¼ tsp(s)
  • Dried cilantro, ½ tsp(s)
  • Cayenne pepper, ¼ tsp(s)
  • Black pepper, 2 dash(es)
  • Paprika, ¼ tsp(s)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Mezze plate with falafels, grilled vegetables & homemade hummus according to recipe instructions below.

Enjoy one serving for dinner. Transfer remaining two servings to an airtight container and keep in the fridge for later in the week.

Mezze plate with falafel, grilled vegetables & homemade hummus instructions

Preheat the broiler to medium-high, then place the bell pepper, asparagus and zucchini on a baking tray and cook for 5 to 6 minutes, turning halfway through, then place to one side and leave to cool. Turn the oven to 350°F.

To make the falafel, in a food processor, blitz 1 cup of the chickpeas, 1 tablespoons of olive oil, ¼ of the lemon juiced, fresh cilantro, psyllium and garlic, as well as the cumin, allspice, dried cilantro and cayenne. Taste, and season with black pepper if desired. Form the mix into 6 small falafels, roughly the same size, and bake for 30 minutes, or until cooked through.

To make the homemade chunky hummus, mash ½ cup of the chickpeas in a small bowl. Add ¼ of the lemon juiced and zested, paprika and 1 tablespoon of olive oil. Alternatively blitz everything in a food processor until it has a chunky 'dip' consistency.

Enjoy 2 falafels and a third of the hummus and vegetable for dinner. Refrigerate the remaining two servings.
NutritionInfo: Calories258Total Fat12.2 g- Saturated Fat1.6 gCholesterol0 mgSodium226 mgTotal Carbohydrate32.1 g- Dietary Fiber10.3 g- Total Sugars10.8 g-- Added Sugars0 gProtein9.5 g

recipeIngredients:
• Extra virgin olive oil, 2 tsp(s) (0.3oz)
  • White onion, chopped, ⅓ cup(s) (1.9oz)
  • Cherry tomatoes, ½ dry pint(s), halved (5.3oz)
  • Roasted red peppers, ¼ cup(s), sliced (1.4oz)
  • Kalamata olives, pitted, ¼ cup(s), halved (1.3oz)
  • Eggs, raw, 3 large egg(s) (5.3oz)
  • Whole-wheat bread, 4 slice(s) (4.5oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Tomato & olive frittata according to recipe instructions below.

Enjoy one serving for breakfast with 2 slices of toast. Store the remaining serving in the fridge for use later in the week.

Tomato & olive frittata instructions

Preheat oven to 400°F.

Heat olive oil in a small, oven-proof skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion and cherry tomatoes and cook 2 to 3 minutes or until lightly golden. Add the roasted pepper and olives to the skillet.

Whisk eggs together in a small bowl, and pour over the vegetables.

Transfer to the oven and bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from oven and slice in half to make 2 servings.

Serve frittata with 2 slices of toast.

recipieName: Peppered steak with balsamic mushroom sauce & steamed greens
recipeIngredients:
• Black pepper, 3 tsp(s), ground (0.2oz)
  • Beef top sirloin steak, any grade, very lean, 6 oz(s), 2 x 3-oz steaks (6oz)
  • Extra virgin olive oil, 4 tsp(s) (0.6oz)
  • Mushrooms, 2 cup(s), whole, mixed, button or brown (6.8oz)
  • Balsamic vinegar, 1 tbsp(s) (0.6oz)
  • Sugar, ¼ tsp(s)
  • Low sodium beef stock, ½ cup(s) (3.9oz)
  • Corn flour, 1 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Parsley, fresh, 2 tbsp(s), chopped (0.3oz)
  • Baby broccoli (broccolini), 1 cup(s), chopped (2.8oz)
  • Snow peas, 1 cup(s), or sugar snap peas, ends trimmed (5.6oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare the Peppered steak with balsamic mushroom sauce & steamed greens according to recipe instructions below.

Enjoy one serving for dinner. Store the remaining serving in an airtight container and place in the fridge for later in the week.

Peppered steak with balsamic mushroom sauce & steamed greens instructions

Preheat oven 350°F. Sprinkle the ground pepper evenly over both steaks, turning to coat both sides. Use your fingertips to press the pepper onto the steaks.

Heat a non-stick skillet over medium-high heat. Add 2 teaspoons oil and sear the steaks for 30 to 40 seconds each side. Remove steaks to a roasting pan. Place into the oven and cook 3 to 4 minutes for medium, or until cooked to your liking. Remove from the oven, cover loosely with foil and let rest for 3 minutes.

Meanwhile, add the remaining 2 teaspoons of oil to the skillet. Add the mushrooms and sauté for 3 minutes or until they start to brown. Add the balsamic vinegar and sugar, cook for 1 minute.

Add 1 tablespoon of the cold broth to the corn flour and mix to a smooth paste. Stir in the remaining broth and mix well. Add corn flour mixture to the mushrooms and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 to 2 minutes or until sauce thickens. Remove from the heat. Stir in the parsley.

Steam or microwave the broccolini and snow peas until bright green and tender.

Place the steak onto serving plates. Spoon over the mushroom sauce and serve with the steamed broccolini and snow peas.

recipieName: Pita pizza with olives & roasted veggies
recipeIngredients:
• Red bell pepper, raw, 1 medium, chopped (4.2oz)
  • Zucchini, ½ medium, cut into ½ inch pieces (3.5oz)
  • Olive oil spray, 6 x two-second spray(s) (0.4oz)
  • Dried mixed herbs, 3 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Whole-wheat pita, 2 large pita(s) (6-1/2" dia) (4.5oz)
  • Tomato paste, 2 tbsp(s) (1.1oz)
  • Cheddar cheese, reduced-fat, shredded, ⅔ cup(s) (2.6oz)
  • Green olives, 24 olive(s) (2.3oz)
  • Basil, fresh, 8 leaf(s) (0.1oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es), to taste
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Pita pizza with olives & roasted veggies according to recipe instructions below.

Serve one pita for lunch today. Transfer remaining pizza to an airtight container and refrigerate for later in the week.

Pita pizza with olives & roasted veggies instructions

Preheat oven to 400°F. Arrange bell pepper and zucchini in a small roasting pan. Spray twice with oil then sprinkle over the dried mixed herbs, turn to coat. Roast for 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

Spray both sides of each pita with oil and place on a baking sheet. Spread tomato paste on pitas. Sprinkle half the cheese over the pitas. Top with roasted vegetables and olives then sprinkle with remaining cheese.

Place baking sheet in the oven for 7 minutes until cheese has melted and pita pockets are warm. Sprinkle each with basil leaves. Season and serve.

TIPS:

  • The vegetables can be roasted up to 3 days ahead. Keep them in an airtight container in the fridge. If you're taking lunch to work, you can prepare the pizza to end of step 2, warm in the microwave or in a sandwich press at work. If heating in a sandwich press place the pizza between two sheets of parchment paper. If you like thinner crust-style pizza, you can flatten the pita pockets with a rolling pin before topping.
  • If you're unable to find dried mixed herbs blend in the supermarket, you can make your own using this recipe: Dried mixed herbs.
